- `GReal t` is defined as `(G.resToImagAxis t).re`.
- `FmodGReal t` is defined as `(FReal t) / (GReal t)`.

The key insight is that `t` is a real number, and when it's used in `F` and `G`, it's implicitly converted to a complex number `t + 0i`. The operation `resToImagAxis` restricts the input to the imaginary axis (i.e., inputs of the form `0 + y i`), but when applied to `t`, which is on the real axis (i.e., `t + 0i`), this operation will essentially evaluate the function at `t`.

